This code uses React functional components with hooks, TypeScript interfaces and types, Tailwind CSS design, and error boundaries and loading states. It also follows accessibility best practices.

Note that this code assumes that you have a FastAPI backend that provides REST APIs for adding, deleting, and toggling tasks. You will need to implement the backend API to complete the application.

Also, this code uses in-memory storage for simplicity. In a real-world application, you would likely want to use a database to store tasks.

You can run the application by executing `npm start` in the project root directory. Open your web browser and navigate to `http://localhost:3000` to see the Todo List application in action.

